    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-02-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="745"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.51/204A.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Minister of Honduras</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-02-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: Referring to my note of the 8th
                    instant, and to our conversation of yesterday, it gives me pleasure to transmit
                    to you the final copies of the bankers’ and fiscal agent contracts relating to
                    the proposed Honduran loan. I am glad to be able to inform you that the
                    Department is now in receipt of a favorable report from the attorneys who were
                    requested by the Department to examine the contracts from the standpoint of
                    Honduras.</p>
                <p>The attorney for the bankers informs the Department, in a letter dated yesterday,
                    that these agreements are now satisfactory to the bankers and that they are
                    prepared to execute the same whenever you are ready to do so.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
